{"filePath": "/docs/api/graphql.md", "content": "# GraphQL API Guide

## Overview

Our GraphQL API provides a flexible, efficient way to query data with a single endpoint.

## Endpoint

```
POST https://api.example.com/graphql
```

## Authentication

```http
POST /graphql
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json
```

## Basic Query

```graphql
query {
  user(id: "123") {
    id
    name
    email
  }
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "data": {
    "user": {
      "id": "123",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "email": "john@example.com"
    }
  }
}
```

## Nested Queries

```graphql
query {
  user(id: "123") {
    id
    name
    orders {
      id
      total
      items {
        product {
          name
          price
        }
        quantity
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Variables

```graphql
query GetUser($userId: ID!) {
  user(id: $userId) {
    id
    name
    email
  }
}
```

**Variables:**
```json
{
  "userId": "123"
}
```

## Mutations

```graphql
mutation {
  createUser(input: {
    name: "Jane Smith"
    email: "jane@example.com"
  }) {
    id
    name
    email
  }
}
```

## Pagination

```graphql
query {
  users(first: 10, after: "cursor123") {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        name
      }
      cursor
    }
    pageInfo {
      hasNextPage
      endCursor
    }
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

```json
{
  "errors": [
    {
      "message": "User not found",
      "path": ["user"],
      "extensions": {
        "code": "NOT_FOUND"
      }
    }
  ]
}
